214
00:10:16,958 --> 00:10:18,958
YOU SOUND LIKE THE
FREAKING POVERTY GOD.

215
00:10:19,041 --> 00:10:24,500
- WHAT DID YOU CALL ME?
- FINE, THEN, HEADS UP.

216
00:10:24,583 --> 00:10:26,750
- LET'S SEE WHAT KIND
OF HAPPINESS MONEY CAN BUY.

217
00:10:26,833 --> 00:10:29,750
YOU CAN USE IT FOR WHATEVER YOU
WANT AND I PROMISE I WON'T TELL.

218
00:10:29,833 --> 00:10:31,791
ONE THING'S FOR SURE. YOU CAN
BUY SOMETHING WAY BETTER

219
00:10:31,875 --> 00:10:33,708
THAN THAT GUNK YOU ATE TONIGHT.

220
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:34,791
- YAY.

221
00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:36,875
- HEY, HOW MUCH DO
YOU THINK THAT IS?

222
00:10:36,958 --> 00:10:39,208
- DON'T EITHER OF YOU
TOUCH THAT. IT'S NOT OURS.

223
00:10:39,291 --> 00:10:40,708
I THINK IT'S TIME FOR YOU TO GO.

224
00:10:40,791 --> 00:10:43,000
- IT'S OKAY, RIKA.

225
00:10:43,083 --> 00:10:45,500
- I APOLOGIZE, ICHIKO.
- WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

226
00:10:46,958 --> 00:10:49,375
- AND I WANT TO APOLOGIZE
TO ALL OF YOU, TOO.

227
00:10:49,458 --> 00:10:53,125
THIS IS MY FAULT, I'M SORRY.
I SHOULDN'T HAVE INVITED HER IN.

228
00:10:54,833 --> 00:10:56,500
- ( grunting )

229
00:10:56,583 --> 00:10:58,666
- GET OUT OF HERE
AND TAKE THAT WITH YOU.

230
00:10:59,333 --> 00:11:00,375
- ( crying )

231
00:11:00,458 --> 00:11:02,750
- KEITA'S MAD.

232
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:05,000
- IDIOT.

233
00:11:05,083 --> 00:11:06,541
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT A BUTTHOLE

234
00:11:06,625 --> 00:11:07,916
YOU JUST MADE
YOURSELF OUT TO BE?

235
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,458
- SHUT UP, POVERTY JERK.

236
00:11:09,541 --> 00:11:11,125
- Ryuta: HOW DID SHE GET HERE?

237
00:11:11,208 --> 00:11:13,791
- WHATEVER. I'M OUT. I DON'T
WANNA BE HERE ANYMORE, ANYWAY.

238
00:11:15,333 --> 00:11:17,583
UGH, WHAT IS WRONG
WITH THAT LOSER?

239
00:11:17,666 --> 00:11:20,208
- (yells ) WHAT'S WRONG
WITH THAT PSYCHO BEAST?

240
00:11:20,291 --> 00:11:22,041
- JUST SAYING. THAT'S WHAT
I'D BE THINKING RIGHT NOW

241
00:11:22,125 --> 00:11:23,541
IF I WAS HIM.

242
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:25,708
DID YOU SEE WHAT HE WAS TRYING
TO MAKE ME EAT FOR DINNER?

243
00:11:25,791 --> 00:11:27,625
UGH. IT'S A LITTLE SAD
HOW CONTENT YOU PRETEND TO BE

244
00:11:27,708 --> 00:11:29,666
WITH THE BITTER, ANGRY TROLL
YOU ARE ON THE INSIDE,

245
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:32,000
BECAUSE I KNOW YOU'D LIKE
TO GROW A HUMAN SOUL ONE DAY.

246
00:11:32,083 --> 00:11:33,458
- LET ME DRY YOUR EYES.

247
00:11:33,541 --> 00:11:36,250
WHAT OTHER PEARLS OF
WISDOM DO YOU HAVE?

248
00:11:36,333 --> 00:11:39,791
- I CAN'T WAIT TO HEAR THEM!
- THAT'S ALL I GOT FOR NOW.

249
00:11:39,875 --> 00:11:43,000
- REALLY SORRY, BABE, I GOT A
JOB TO DO AND UNFORTUNATELY,

250
00:11:43,083 --> 00:11:45,166
THAT DOESN'T INCLUDE
PERSONAL THERAPY SESSIONS

251
00:11:45,250 --> 00:11:46,666
FOR YOUR FAKE LOVE LIFE.

252
00:11:46,750 --> 00:11:50,125
- IT'S NOT FAKE. WHY IS EVERYONE
IN SUCH A BAD MOOD TODAY?

253
00:12:01,166 --> 00:12:03,125
- Woman: LOOK AT THOSE CLOUDS.
WE BETTER GET HOME.

254
00:12:03,208 --> 00:12:06,541
- YEAH, KINDA LOOKS LIKE
THERE'S A TYPHOON ON THE WAY.

255
00:12:06,625 --> 00:12:09,791
- UGH. I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT
TURD IS STILL GETTING TO ME.

256
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:11,833
THIS IS TOTALLY
RUINING MY DAY OFF.

257
00:12:11,916 --> 00:12:14,083
- LOOK, THERE'S
THE PSYCHO BEAST.

258
00:12:14,166 --> 00:12:16,125
- HUH? IT'S TSUWABUKI'S
HOUSE BRAT.

259
00:12:16,208 --> 00:12:19,000
- MY BROTHER TOLD ME PEOPLE LIKE
YOU WHO WORSHIP MONEY ARE CRAZY,

260
00:12:19,083 --> 00:12:21,208
AND WILL NEVER HAVE ANY FRIENDS
UNLESS YOU BUY THEM.

261
00:12:21,291 --> 00:12:23,291
SO, WE ALL CALL YOU
THE PSYCHO BEAST.

262
00:12:23,375 --> 00:12:26,166
- THAT'S CUTE AND ALL, BUT I DO
HAVE A NAME. IT'S ICHIKO SAKURA.

263
00:12:26,250 --> 00:12:27,583
- YEAH, AND THEY
ALL CALL YOU THAT

264
00:12:27,666 --> 00:12:28,791
BECAUSE YOUR JUGS
ARE SO ENORMOUS.

265
00:12:28,875 --> 00:12:30,750
- I SAID ICHIKO,
NOT "TIT-CHIKO",

266
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:32,041
YOU PERVERTED LITTLE BRAT.

267
00:12:32,125 --> 00:12:33,750
I'M GONNA GRIND THAT NAME
OUT OF YOUR MEMORY.

268
00:12:33,833 --> 00:12:35,333
- AW MAN, I HAVE
THIS ONE ALREADY.

269
00:12:35,416 --> 00:12:37,875
- HEY! DON'T THROW IT AWAY.
I'LL TAKE IT!

270
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:40,583
- RIGHT. YOU SHOULD TRY TO BUY
YOUR OWN ONCE IN A WHILE.

271
00:12:40,666 --> 00:12:43,166
- DO YOU HAVE ANY CARDS YOU
HAVEN'T MOOCHED OFF OTHER KIDS?

272
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,708
- YES, IT'S PERFECT.

273
00:12:46,791 --> 00:12:48,458
I GET THE SIBS ON
MY SIDE TELLING HIM

274
00:12:48,541 --> 00:12:49,833
WHAT A HORRIBLE
MISTAKE HE'S MADE,

275
00:12:49,916 --> 00:12:52,333
AND THEN HE'LL BE AT MY FEET
BEGGING FOR FORGIVENESS.

276
00:12:52,416 --> 00:12:53,625
OH, DON'T BE SILLY.

277
00:12:53,708 --> 00:12:55,208
WHY DON'T YOU LET YOUR BIG
SISTER HOOK YOU UP?

278
00:12:55,291 --> 00:12:57,000
- WHAT? YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

279
00:12:57,083 --> 00:12:59,250
I DIDN'T ASK YOU
TO BUY ME THOSE.

280
00:12:59,333 --> 00:13:01,333
- COME ON, JUST OPEN IT
AND CHECK THEM OUT.

281
00:13:01,416 --> 00:13:03,833
IF THE CARDS SUCK, THROW THEM
AWAY. IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

282
00:13:05,708 --> 00:13:07,250
- ( gasps )

283
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:09,833
- WHOA, THAT'S AWESOME. YOU
GOT ONE OF THE SUPER-RARE ONES.

284
00:13:09,916 --> 00:13:11,500
- YEAH, IN YOUR
FIRST PACK, EVEN.

285
00:13:11,583 --> 00:13:13,416
- AREN'T YOU GLAD YOU TOOK
A RISK AND OPENED IT?

286
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:16,875
- THAT'S WHAT WE CALL
HAPPINESS ENERGY AT WORK, FOLKS.

287
00:13:16,958 --> 00:13:20,041
- THANKS A LOT. UM,
THAT WAS REALLY COOL OF YOU.

288
00:13:20,125 --> 00:13:23,875
- ( smirks ) NOT WHAT YOU EXPECT
FROM A PSYCHO BEAST, IS IT?

289
00:13:23,958 --> 00:13:25,291
- I DON'T KNOW ABOUT THAT.

290
00:13:25,375 --> 00:13:27,625
I WAS TOLD THAT WHENEVER
ANYONE DOES SOMETHING NICE

291
00:13:27,708 --> 00:13:29,916
THAT YOU SHOULD SAY THANK YOU,
NO MATTER WHO THEY ARE.

292
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,916
SO, I DON'T KNOW IF YOU'RE
REALLY A PSYCHO OR NOT,

293
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:33,250
BUT I WANTED TO BE POLITE.

294
00:13:33,333 --> 00:13:37,375
- ( chuckles ) IT'S OKAY.
I ACCEPT YOUR APOLOGY.

295
00:13:37,458 --> 00:13:40,416
- I DIDN'T APOLOGIZE,
BUT, THANKS, TIT-CHIKO!

296
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:43,416
- ( yells ) WHAT DID I TELL YOU?
MY NAME IS ICHIKO!

297
00:13:43,500 --> 00:13:45,041
- ( screaming )

298
00:13:45,125 --> 00:13:48,083
- LOOK AT ALL THOSE POWERS.
- LET ME SEE IT AGAIN.

299
00:13:48,166 --> 00:13:49,708
- I DON'T KNOW HOW
MANY PACKS I'VE BOUGHT

300
00:13:49,791 --> 00:13:51,208
LOOKING FOR THAT ONE.

301
00:13:51,291 --> 00:13:53,166
- NOT EXACTLY
THE PRIMARY TARGET,

302
00:13:53,250 --> 00:13:55,416
BUT IT DID KINDA FEEL GOOD
TO HELP HIM OUT, I GUESS.

303
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:56,791
I'M COOL WITH THAT.

304
00:13:57,875 --> 00:14:00,500
- EVEN CRAZY TIT-CHIKO
HAS A GOOD SIDE.

305
00:14:00,583 --> 00:14:02,833
( gasps ) WHAT AM I
GOING TO TELL KEITA?

306
00:14:02,916 --> 00:14:04,958
I CAN'T TELL HIM THE PSYCHO
HAG BOUGHT IT FOR ME.

307
00:14:05,041 --> 00:14:06,958
HE'LL BE PISSED. HUH.

308
00:14:07,041 --> 00:14:10,750
- AH, PLEASE DON'T FALL DOWN
IN THERE. NO.

309
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:12,166
UGH, I HATE MY LIFE.

310
00:14:14,541 --> 00:14:16,291
THERE'S NO WAY
I'M GONNA FIND IT.

311
00:14:16,375 --> 00:14:19,625
IT'S TOO DARK. AND IT SMELLS!

312
00:14:19,708 --> 00:14:21,625
- WELL, THAT CAN'T BE SAFE.

313
00:14:21,708 --> 00:14:25,375
WOW, I GUESS THEY MUST BE DOING
SOME WORK IN THE SEWERS.

314
00:14:25,458 --> 00:14:27,666
- I CAN'T BELIEVE
I ACTUALLY FOUND IT.

315
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:30,625
I'LL JUST WIPE IT OFF
AND IT'LL BE GOOD AS NEW.

316
00:14:30,708 --> 00:14:34,208
- ( exclaims ) OH MY GOSH.
SOMEONE CLOSED IT?

317
00:14:37,375 --> 00:14:38,958
- Tsuwabuki: I'M HOME.

318
00:14:39,041 --> 00:14:40,708
WHAT'S UP WITH ALL THIS RAIN?

319
00:14:40,791 --> 00:14:42,708
- HEY, UH, RYU'S GONE

320
00:14:42,791 --> 00:14:44,625
AND I CAN'T REACH HIM ON
HIS CELL PHONE.

321
00:14:44,708 --> 00:14:47,458
I'VE CALLED ALL OF HIS FRIENDS
AND NO ONE HAS HEARD ANYTHING.

322
00:14:47,541 --> 00:14:49,666
IT'S GETTING LATE. I'M WORRIED.

323
00:14:49,750 --> 00:14:51,250
- ME TOO.

324
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:54,458
- I WISH KEITA WAS HERE.
THIS IS SO SCARY.

325
00:14:54,541 --> 00:14:59,708
- ( screams ) RYUTA, CAN YOU
HEAR ME? RYUTA, WHERE ARE YOU?

326
00:15:02,416 --> 00:15:04,541
THERE'S GOTTA BE
SOMEONE ELSE I CAN CALL.

327
00:15:04,625 --> 00:15:08,291
SOMEONE HAS TO KNOW WHERE HE
IS. THIS IS CRAZY.

328
00:15:08,375 --> 00:15:10,458
- ( gasps ) SPEAKING OF CRAZY...

329
00:15:10,541 --> 00:15:11,583
- ( door bell ringing )

330
00:15:12,958 --> 00:15:15,375
- IS SOMEONE SERIOUSLY
AT MY DOOR THIS LATE?

331
00:15:15,458 --> 00:15:16,791
HUH? NO WAY!

332
00:15:19,083 --> 00:15:21,500
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?
YOU LOOK LIKE A DROWNED RAT.

333
00:15:21,583 --> 00:15:24,208
- I'M TRYING TO FIND MY BROTHER.
I THOUGHT HE MIGHT'VE COME HERE.

334
00:15:24,291 --> 00:15:25,583
- WELL, YOU THOUGHT WRONG.

335
00:15:25,666 --> 00:15:27,916
HEY, DON'T WORRY ABOUT THANKING
ME FOR THE CARD.

336
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:30,041
- HUH? WHAT IS THAT
SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

337
00:15:30,125 --> 00:15:32,250
DID HE ASK YOU TO BUY ONE OF
THOSE CARD PACKETS FOR HIM?

338
00:15:32,333 --> 00:15:34,875
- OF COURSE NOT. I OFFERED.

339
00:15:34,958 --> 00:15:37,833
- HOW MUCH WAS IT?
- THREE HUNDRED YEN.

340
00:15:40,625 --> 00:15:42,166
- ( sighs ) THAT'S RIDICULOUS.

341
00:15:42,250 --> 00:15:44,208
I COULD'VE JUST BOUGHT
THAT FOR HIM MYSELF.

342
00:15:44,291 --> 00:15:46,250
- IT SEEMS LIKE YOU'RE
MORE THAN JUST A BIG BROTHER

343
00:15:46,333 --> 00:15:47,125
TO THESE GUYS.

344
00:15:47,208 --> 00:15:50,083
- HUH? MAYBE SO.

345
00:15:50,166 --> 00:15:52,708
I HATE TO ADMIT IT, BUT A LOT
OF WHAT YOU SAID MADE SENSE.

346
00:15:52,791 --> 00:15:54,375
I JUST WISH I COULD
GIVE THEM MORE.

347
00:15:54,458 --> 00:15:57,000
THE ONE THING RYU WANTS MORE
THAN ANYTHING IS TO PLAY SOCCER.

348
00:15:57,083 --> 00:15:59,958
BUT I CAN'T AFFORD THE CLUB
FEES, THE BALL, ANY OF IT.

349
00:16:01,500 --> 00:16:03,625
INSTEAD HE PLAYS
USED VIDEO GAMES.

350
00:16:03,708 --> 00:16:05,250
I WISH I COULD BUY
RIKA HER OWN DESK,

351
00:16:05,333 --> 00:16:07,541
SO SHE WOULDN'T HAVE TO STUDY
IN THE KITCHEN.

352
00:16:07,625 --> 00:16:09,166
IT'D BE NICE IF MIKA AND SORATA

353
00:16:09,250 --> 00:16:11,250
DIDN'T HAVE TO WEAR
HAND-ME-DOWNS.

354
00:16:11,333 --> 00:16:13,208
I'M NOT SAYING WE NEED
A CRAP-TON OF MONEY

355
00:16:13,291 --> 00:16:14,458
IN ORDER TO BE HAPPY.

356
00:16:14,541 --> 00:16:16,958
BUT NOT HAVING ANY OF IT
MAKES THINGS SO HARD!

357
00:16:17,041 --> 00:16:19,416
- ASK YOUR FRIENDS FOR HELP.
THAT'S WHY WE'RE HERE.

358
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:21,750
- WELL, IT ISN'T THAT EASY
FOR ME TO DO.

359
00:16:21,833 --> 00:16:23,541
- WHY NOT?

360
00:16:23,625 --> 00:16:25,666
- I WANNA SHOW MY SIBLINGS
THAT THEY DON'T NEED TO BE

361
00:16:25,750 --> 00:16:27,375
LIKE EVERYONE ELSE
TO HAVE A QUALITY LIFE.

362
00:16:27,458 --> 00:16:29,041
THERE'S NOTHING WRONG
WITH HAVING TO WORK

363
00:16:29,125 --> 00:16:31,041
FOR EVERYTHING YOU HAVE.

364
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:32,416
IF THEY LEARN TO RELY
ON THEMSELVES,

365
00:16:32,500 --> 00:16:34,000
THEY CAN'T BE LET DOWN.

366
00:16:36,500 --> 00:16:39,125
BESIDES, YOU'RE THE LAST PERSON
I'D ASK FOR HELP.

367
00:16:42,083 --> 00:16:43,583
- ( swishing )

368
00:16:43,666 --> 00:16:47,041
- OH, GREAT. GO ON AND LECTURE
ME AND MAKE ME FEEL EVEN WORSE.

369
00:16:48,541 --> 00:16:49,916
- THAT'S NOT WHY I'M HERE.

370
00:16:52,791 --> 00:16:54,333
- THEN PLEASE ENLIGHTEN ME.

371
00:16:56,166 --> 00:16:59,833
HEY, WHAT'RE YOU DOING?
AND WHAT DID YOU PUT ON MY HEAD?

372
00:16:59,916 --> 00:17:04,208
- LISTEN CAREFULLY.
- HUH? I'M LOST. LISTEN TO WHAT?

373
00:17:06,166 --> 00:17:08,458
- Ryuta: HELP ME!

374
00:17:08,541 --> 00:17:11,000
- Momiji: RYUTA IS TRAPPED
IN A PRETTY TIGHT SPOT.

375
00:17:11,083 --> 00:17:12,833
YOU'LL NEED TO FOLLOW HIS VOICE.

376
00:17:18,166 --> 00:17:20,041
- ALMOST.
( screams )

377
00:17:20,125 --> 00:17:22,666
- ( exclaims ) RYU.

378
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:24,583
- I KNOW THIS IS GOING
TO BLOW YOUR MIND,

379
00:17:24,666 --> 00:17:26,250
BUT THE LOUDER HIS VOICE
SOUNDS IN YOUR EAR,

380
00:17:26,333 --> 00:17:27,750
THE CLOSER YOU ARE TO HIM.

381
00:17:27,833 --> 00:17:29,958
- YEAH, I FIGURED
THAT MUCH. THANKS.

382
00:17:30,041 --> 00:17:31,875
- ONE MORE THING.
REMEMBER THIS?

383
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:35,875
- ( gasps ) I THINK SO.

384
00:17:35,958 --> 00:17:38,166
- CHECK IT OUT.
THIS IS THE POINT OF OUR CHAT.

385
00:17:38,250 --> 00:17:40,208
WHAT IF I TOLD YOU, YOU
COULD SAVE THAT BOY'S LIFE

386
00:17:40,291 --> 00:17:43,125
BY USING YOUR OWN
HAPPINESS ENERGY?

387
00:17:43,208 --> 00:17:44,583
YOU WOULD HAVE TO
GIVE IT AWAY FREELY

388
00:17:44,666 --> 00:17:45,875
BECAUSE YOU WANTED TO HELP,

389
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,875
NOT BECAUSE YOU'RE
EXPECTING TO GET SOMETHING.

390
00:17:47,958 --> 00:17:49,875
IF A MIRACLE HAPPENS
AND YOU PULL THAT OFF,

391
00:17:49,958 --> 00:17:51,541
I'LL HAVE EFFECTIVELY
DONE MY JOB.

392
00:17:53,208 --> 00:17:54,541
OH, WELL.

393
00:17:54,625 --> 00:17:55,833
YOU'VE ALREADY MADE
IT PERFECTLY CLEAR

394
00:17:55,916 --> 00:17:58,041
THAT NO ONE ELSE MATTERS TO YOU
EXCEPT SUWANO.

395
00:17:58,125 --> 00:17:59,791
ME AND MY DUMB IDEAS.

396
00:17:59,875 --> 00:18:02,500
- THANKS A LOT. UM,
THAT WAS REALLY COOL OF YOU.

397
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:07,583
- NICE TRY. BUT YOU'RE
NOT GONNA GUILT ME

398
00:18:07,666 --> 00:18:10,166
INTO FEELING BAD
ABOUT WHAT I SAID.

399
00:18:10,250 --> 00:18:13,125
- NAH, YOU HAD A PRETTY DECENT
POINT ABOUT THE POWER OF CASH.

400
00:18:13,208 --> 00:18:14,333
- THEY'RE WRONG ABOUT ME.

401
00:18:14,416 --> 00:18:16,500
I WANTED THEM TO REGRET
WHAT THEY SAID.

402
00:18:16,583 --> 00:18:19,791
- LOOKS LIKE THIS IS
THE PERFECT OPPORTUNITY, THEN.

403
00:18:19,875 --> 00:18:23,833
- SCREW IT. I DON'T NEED TO
RISK CARING ABOUT ANYONE ELSE.

404
00:18:23,916 --> 00:18:25,416
- SO YOU'RE GONNA
LEAVE HIM OUT THERE?

405
00:18:33,041 --> 00:18:34,375
PLEASE. YOU'RE NOT THAT CRUEL.

406
00:18:34,458 --> 00:18:37,041
RYUTA ISN'T JUST ANYONE ELSE
AND YOU KNOW IT.

407
00:18:39,708 --> 00:18:42,791
- FINE. BUT CAN I TELL YOU
SOMETHING?

408
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:46,583
- ( screams ) TAKING ORDERS FROM
YOU KINDA REALLY TICKS ME OFF!

409
00:18:46,666 --> 00:18:47,958
- AW, POOR BABY.

410
00:18:52,708 --> 00:18:54,541
KILLING.

411
00:18:56,000 --> 00:18:57,666
THAT'S WHAT WE CALL
A "WHACK JOB".

412
00:18:59,416 --> 00:19:02,375
- YEAH, PEOPLE FOR THE MOST
PART ARE DESPICABLE CREATURES.

413
00:19:02,458 --> 00:19:05,916
BUT STILL. ONCE IN A WHILE
THEY SURPRISE ME.

414
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,791
- RYU, CAN YOU HEAR ME?
- Ryuta: I'M OVER HERE.

415
00:19:10,583 --> 00:19:12,125
- WHAT THE...

416
00:19:12,208 --> 00:19:15,291
YOU IDIOT. DON'T MOVE, I'LL
BE RIGHT THERE. JUST HOLD ON.

417
00:19:15,375 --> 00:19:16,500
- ( whimpering )

418
00:19:19,833 --> 00:19:22,916
- HERE, GRAB MY HAND.
COME ON, REACH.

419
00:19:27,458 --> 00:19:28,500
- ( gasps )

420
00:19:28,583 --> 00:19:29,708
- ( screams )

421
00:19:30,625 --> 00:19:33,791
- ( screams ) RYU! ICHIKO?

422
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:38,375
- ( panting )

423
00:19:38,458 --> 00:19:40,083
- AM I REALLY DOING THIS?

424
00:19:40,166 --> 00:19:43,750
I CAN'T BELIEVE I WILLINGLY TOOK
ORDERS FROM THAT POVERTY CREEP.

425
00:19:43,833 --> 00:19:48,208
THIS KID ISN'T WORTH IT.
HE'S NOT WORTH IT.

426
00:19:48,291 --> 00:19:51,416
